    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of Larix kaempferi, native to Japan, but planted in Europe and the United Kingdom. The reddish brown timber in similar to that of the European larch, and it also used in the construction of poles and boat planks.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
